===Etymology===
Borrowed from {{bor|en|fro|vouel}} ({{cog|fr|voyelle}}), from {{der|en|la|vōcālis||voiced}}, a [[:semantic loan|semantic loan]] of {{noncog|grc-koi|φωνῆεν}}. {{doublet|en|vocal}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{enPR|vouʹəl}}, {{IPA|en|/ˈvaʊ.əl/}}
* {{a|also}} {{enPR|voul}}, {{IPA|en|/vaʊl/}}
* {{audio|en|en-us-vowel.ogg|Audio (US)}}
* {{rhymes|en|aʊəl|aʊl}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{lb|en|phonetics}} A sound produced by the [[vocal cords]] with relatively little restriction of the [[oral cavity]], forming the prominent sound of a [[syllable]].
# {{lb|en|orthography}} A [[letter]] representing the sound of vowel; in English, the vowels are ''a'', ''e'', ''i'', ''o'', ''u'', and sometimes ''y''.

